RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT SILENCE stalked in the three path, challenged from outside with three furlongs remaining, took over late on the far turn, cleared at the top of the lane, remained clear to the sixteenth pole and held. BOGINSKAYA broke out, chased three wide at the back into the first turn, got boxed in three deep on the far turn, continued three wide into the lane, chased after the winner through the lane, put in a late bid but was not enough. DORINE'S WILD CAT traveled along the inside off the pace, moved off the inside and into range in the middle stages, chased between rivals in the two path on the far turn, moved to the inside in the stretch and finished evenly late. ROUND IN CIRCLES showed keen early speed while in the two path, set the pace to the far turn, challenged at the three-eighths pole, gave up command leaving that bend and weakened. GEEJAYTEE broke out, tracked four wide early, went four deep into the second bend, spun five wide into the lane and weakened. FAST INVESTMENT forwardly placed on the inside early, coaxed around the second bend continuing to hug the rail, moved out in upper stretch and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Fast Investment
ENTRY.OWNER: Anderson Richard Knapp Steve R and Peal Larry

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Silence
ENTRY.OWNER: Bowden David E and Bowden Tracie D

ENTRY.NAME: Boginskaya
ENTRY.OWNER: Branch William A and Hill Arnold R
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, chased 3wide, boxed 3deep 2nd, late bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 21000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Kline Carolyn Kline William and Stevens Satchell

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROMAN EMPRESS stalked three wide into the turn, came four wide into the drive, bid four deep between rivals midstretch and proved best late. AWESOME TAYLOR got crowded a bit shortly after that the start, chased four then five wide around the turn, had the rider lost the whip while offering a challenge five deep in upper stretch, kept to task under hand urging and got outkicked by the winner. VEGAN stalked two to three wide on the turn, bid between rivals at the top of the lane, took over midstretch but got outkicked in the late stages. TROPICANA GIRL stumbled badly and brushed with inner rival, went up to duel from inside, fought two wide into the lane, battled on down the stretch and faltered late. QUIET SECRETARY dueled for command from outside, inched ahead at the five-sixteenths pole, lost command near the three-sixteenths pole and weakened. DRIZELLA was unprepared and tossed her head at the start, trailed on the inside to the stretch and failed to menace. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT DRIZELLA WAS NOT AWARDED A FAIR START AND IS RULED A NON-STARTER.

ENTRY.NAME: Drizella
ENTRY.OWNER: Alvarez Edwin G and Lopez Miguel
ENTRY.COMMENT: unprepared start, trailed inside, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Vegan
ENTRY.OWNER: Medina Lizbeth and Cisneros Araceli M

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Taylor
ENTRY.OWNER: Great Friends Stables LLC and Davis Mark
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit crowded early, chased 4-5wide, lost whip upper, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Quiet Secretary
ENTRY.OWNER: Clarke M Cooper Family Trust and Cooper Rockie Lynne

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WOK DON'T RUN dueled for command from outside, got floated out by CAPO SORELLA into the stretch, battled with rivals on both sides through the final furlong and dug in to gamely prevail. LIGHTING AND REIGN chased two wide outside a rival into the turn, tipped out leaving the bend, moved back towards the rail and rallied inside the top trio but got denied. MISS PIXY STIX brushed the gate, stalked four wide into the turn, cut into the three path early on the bend, floated back out entering the stretch, launched a bid three deep at the three-sixteenths pole but was also denied in the end. CAPO SORELLA away quickly to take the front, dueled from inside with WOK DON'T RUN, drifted out into the stretch, fought into the final furlong and yielded in deep stretch. HURRICANE HOTTIE chased along the inside, dropped back around the turn and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Lighting and Reign
ENTRY.OWNER: Halasz Thomas E Knapp Steve R and Lovingier Terry C
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2wide, tipped out, bid inside, denied

ENTRY.NAME: Capo Sorella
ENTRY.COMMENT: away quickly, dueled inside, drifted into str, faltered

ENTRY.NAME: Wok Don't Run
ENTRY.OWNER: California Racing Partners Ciaglia Racing LLC Cheung Daniel and Pearson Richard
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled outside, floated into str, dug in

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 97. Claiming Purse 30000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEPARTURE rated in the two path early while under pressure, showed the way four wide into the stretch, asked left handed in upper stretch and powered away. HEIR (FR) chased three wide early, went two wide into the far turn, angled out into the stretch, showed a mild rally and edged MY INDY for second. MY INDY chased five wide around the clubhouse turn, raced three wide outside a rival on the second bend, steered out approaching the stretch, churned on down the lane and got edged for second. HIGH HEATER pressed from outside in the three path, kept the pressure on three then four wide on the far turn, proved no match for the winner in upper stretch and flattened to fourth. BLAMELESS pulled early in the four path early, continued to tug up the backstretch, remained wide through the far turn and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Departure
ENTRY.OWNER: Terry Mike Anderson Mike T and Clyde Terry D
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated 2path, led 4wide into str, powered away

ENTRY.NAME: Blameless
ENTRY.OWNER: Haagsma John R and Vanderdussen Robert John

ENTRY.NAME: My Indy
ENTRY.OWNER: A and J Racing and R and K Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST A LITTLE LUCK vied for the lead between rivals, inched ahead into the turn, shook free past the quarter pole and was ridden out. MODERA became fractious in the gate, chased from inside then two wide into the turn, climbed around the bend, moved out in the final furlong and gained second. R GIRL'S WERTH IT broke out and bumped rival, pressed from inside, fought with the winner to the quarter pole, could not go on with that rival after and flattened to third. ILA VEIW TOO pressed three deep between rivals then chased three wide into the turn, spun four wide into the stretch and weakened. MANGO MOON vied four deep then three deep leaving the backstretch, chased the top pair past the three-eighths pole and faded. HOUSE OF TARGARYEN took a bump from inside at the start, climbed a bit early, chased two then three wide at the back on the turn before angling out into the lane and failed to menace. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION, THE FIFTH RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Modera
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, chased inside, climbed turn, 2wide, gained 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: House of Targaryen
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, climbed early, 2-3wide, angled out, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Just a Little Luck
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, cleared, drew off, ridden out

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Terry Knight, Jean Annuzzi & Mel Annuzzi

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 87. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUTY FIRST stalked from inside, challenged entering the lane, took over at the quarter pole, kicked clear from outer rival, asked a few times right handed at the eighth pole and was ridden out to the wire. LOGON TO WIN raced up close early, had to check between rivals entering the turn, angled out and came five wide into the stretch and rallied for the place honors. CRIBBAGE BOARD set the tone up the backstretch, led three wide into the lane, lost command with a quarter mile left to run and flattened to third. QUINCEY traveled near the back off the rail, angled into the two path early on the bend, came back out approaching the stretch and kept on to round out the superfecta. THE LAST ONE PERK broke a step slow, moved inside for the turn, spun three wide into the stretch and lacked a rally. MOON ICE tracked off the rail, angled to the inside for the turn, steered back out entering the lane and weakened. FORDY G pressed from outside up the backstretch, chased three to four wide on the turn and weakened. SMILING RULER broke a step slow, climbed early on, trailed four wide into the drive and failed to make an impact.

ENTRY.NAME: Duty First
ENTRY.OWNER: Valpredo Donald J and Valpredo Sally
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, kicked clear, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Smiling Ruler
ENTRY.OWNER: Robison J Kirk and Robison Judy

ENTRY.NAME: Logon to Win
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close, checked between 7/16, angled out, gained 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 104. Starter Allowance Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEE THROUGH IT dueled for the lead from inside, cleared outer rival at the eighth pole and edged away. MOOSE MITCHELL dueled for command from outside, could not kick on with the winner approaching the eighth pole and stayed on to hold second. LOVESICK BLUES stalked outside a rival, rounded the bend three then four wide, finished willingly through the final furlong but needed to find more late. SWIFT AS I AM chased three deep into the turn, came five wide into the lane and lacked the needed response. PERFECTIONISTIC stalked the dueling leaders two wide into the turn, moved to the rail around the bend and weakened down the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: See Through It
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth

ENTRY.NAME: Perfectionistic
ENTRY.OWNER: The Ellwood Johnston Trust Hilvers Mary Hilvers Peter and Tevelde Kenneth A

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEAHAWK MARY bumped on both sides at the start, went up to duel outside JUST IS, cleared that rival leaving the turn, drifted out in the lane and was kept to task to the wire. HEY DEMPS brushed inner rival, pressed three deep between foes up the backstretch, chased the leaders three then four wide on the turn and could not rally in the lane. YVETT'S SURPRISE broke a step slow from outside, went four then five wide on the turn, improved position in the lane but failed to threaten. ILLHAVEANOTHERKISS raced up close four deep between then chased leaving the backstretch, angled to the rail on the turn and weakened down the lane.
